<br>
Trak has 32 k hps.<br>
<br>
Land 20 2 k nukes on trak, and you win.<br>
<br>
Land 10 4 k nukes on trak, and you win.<br>
<br>
Land 5 8 k nukes on trak, and you win.<br>
<br>
Of course, melee-range restrictions on nukes, resist debuffing, etc, all make the above hard.<br>
<br>
A nuke half the size can't pull off the MB effect, even if it is twice as fast and as efficient.  Meanwhile, in less extreme examples, that smaller nuke is just as good for the wizard.<br>
<br>
Hence, smaller faster casting nukes.<br>
<br>
Rains require a stationary mob, and time, to be useful.  Hence, rains can and should be better than nukes.<br>
