<br>
Now, about big nukes. It simply impress people and thats it. I am a 63 wizard with 106AA. And of all my career being a wizard, I never solod. Surprised? No since soloing sux, boring and if I have to solo, then I go play another single player game which is more entertaining. About big nukes, I am one of the 2 wizards in my guild and I do not own AT, GSS and EER (though will probably soon once I get hold of those runes for research). We are allianced with another guild who has 3 wizards, which 2 of them are 65 and have access to AT. Sure their nukes are big, and I see 5k crits all the time. I think they got drought of E'ci aswell. I have sunstrike, but guess what? I never use it any more except just for finishing off some gating mob which requires fast killing in very short time. ( but still rarely use it since I got drought of thunder)<br>
<br>
What I am using is Isos, and DoR all the time. Maybe Drought of Thunder for those annoying Cleric mobs and gating mobs to prevent them from casting. I own a haste staff (from the mech dragon in PoI forgot name... too bad its 2hb <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), and I cast DoR in 2.5sec, Isos in 3.1 sec. I am chain casting these 2 spells constantly and I get more crits than any other wizards in the alliance guild. I own the highest DPS! Yes you heard me highest! All guild rogues wields ssra, pop, Ntov, primal weapons with access to best haste and haste gear. Rangers have AM3 etc blah blah and such. <br>
But I still can out damage them with my crappy gear. Compared with 2 wizards owning AT. I outdamaged them by 3 times. I rarely get summoned due to concussion. DoR and Isos price are a joke, seen them going as low as 1k for DoR and Isos... uh well those are actually been given out.<br>
<br>
My gear? Well I got FT2 from gear. Most of them comes from my AA points. Imp fam, epic, mc3. My mana pool is about 3800 according to magelo, nothing surprising and most of my gear are very much obtainable. My arms are from ME, I think toilers. The head... ug yes its from PoF (laugh), the bracer, Ear and neck are from JC. The pants is from UP. Boots is from ToV, and its not actually that good. I use it for mana. Potc ear, well you can get all the compo for around 6k these days. Just buying each pieces when i got cash. 2ndary item is the quest in WL. Can be done solo AND in 1 day. And its very nice. The only, and I repeat the only RAID item I got is the CT robe, the sash which is from Acrylia Caverns and the ring which is the emp key. (well I call it farming but oh well) <br>
<br>
I share the pain that you cannot find groups. But I see this problem is not the wizards part but its because from other people's prespective of viewing the wizards. Most people in this board (appart from the fact that they are being a wizard) knows the value of a wizard. Also I believe the friends and guildies that they are grouping also knows how potential a wizard can be. But some people doesn't see it that way. Maybe because they saw a wizard use large nuke ( pre 60s and post 49) and med nearly all the time. I have seen those types of wizards myself. Also I have seen the same thing in the guild too. Yesterday Velketor was up. And I called out the guild that he was up and maybe we can take him down ( so that I had a chance for my conflag robe which i think its still usefull to have a non mana cost DD ). My guild agreed, but the alliance guild did not. They said that he drops nothing good except 1 item ( which i presume was a melee gear ) and they had planned to go to Sleepers Tomb after taking down King Tormax, Statue and Idol. Was shocked myself how little value they put to casters. Maybe they didn't know about the gear they drop is usefull to the casters ( yes not only wizards, mage drop is good aswell i recall drops a clicable DD boots )<br>
but I kept my mouth shut. We alliance have gone too far and I did not want to put our relation into vain just for me being unreasonable to the other guild bacause of one mob. ( and yes I do NOT own the ST key. Hell I am not even in the list of obtaining the key... + the wizards are on the bottom of the list )<br>
<br>
I believe my guild + alliance guild simply sees the casters as extra damage imput. And /chucle I think thats why they could take down Grummus but not Aerin'Dar. You see, in PoP you require more caster power than melee. Simply to end the fight faster. Yes melee, rogue and even rangers can have a high dps, but not as high as a caster. You cannot relly alot from the cleric heals because of how the mob hit SO hard in pop and to MULTIPLE people that eighther the attackers die fast, or ma dies because of out of mana. I have seen this. I have been temporarely in a very strong Euro guild. They had alot of mages, wizards and I have seen the burst power that we casters can provide. I came back to my old guild due to RL issues and I was forced to be casual player. And saw the difference. <br>
<br>
Ugh... why my post become so long? Anyway to the first poster, try grouping with your guild more. If you are not then try joining one. Family type guild is a good start. Many of my guildies makes alt but they never make a caster type ( due to its... poor starting compared to a twink melee ). Almost all my alts are casters, except a coupel which are 59war 53 sham and 53 cleric. I enjoy playing the mage, alot. Ugh... chanters are so hard to play heh and so hard to exp soloing. ( charm solo ugh.. the horror ) Casters are not broke, not to mention wizards are not broke. Now that the new research has been introduced, you have more chance of getting those ever wanted GSS, EER and other spells you ever dreamed of. Have faith in your class that you rolled. And uh, never compare EQ casters with another RPG. They are totally different. Then again EQ is hardly an RPG anyway :P<br>
