<br>
To the poster that said old wizards had it easier:<br>
No familiar<br>
No flowing thought<br>
No focus effects<br>
No aa<br>
No Dragonbane<br>
No Giantbane<br>
No Snare<br>
<br>
You can take your &quot;easier&quot; and shove it right up your ass.  It was our work and determination in sticking with the class we love, without turning into whiny ass kunark rangers or paladins, that got you all of your toys.  Countless hours of discussions on graffe.com, countless feedbacks with ideas, and an immense ammount of work to come up with ideas that didnt break the shit out of our class, and actually made it balanced.<br>
<br>
We don't have any new rains, pbaoe, etc. because we don't need them.  Mobs in PoP have significantly fewer hp than luclin and velious, and are designed with pbaoe out of the question in the first place.<br>
<br>
There was a time when as a wizard, you could nuke an xp mob, and its health wouldn't move.  THATS when wizards were broken.  We had nothing to offer raids or xp groups.  WE dealt with that shit, and STILL progressed.<br>
<br>
Tweaks are all we need now, and really only at certain levels.  And regardless of what is tweaked, it still isn't going to give any of you whiners enough personality to be accepted into a good xp group.  There is an aura of self-loathing that just seeps from your posts, and I'm sure it is the same way when you go LFG. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=assassinite>Assassinite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/26/03 10:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>rogues arent limited by mana, and have at least SOME defensive skills.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
