 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=targonis>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 747<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/27/03 8:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: old times it was easier ?</span><hr size=1> The original poster had a valid point, two draughts DO take longer to cast than one ice comet, though the damage you do with those two draughts IS a bit higher than a single cast of ice comet, ONLY because Verant put a damage cap on ice comet.<br>
<br>
Draught of ice at 57 is a nice boost over previous draughts though, that was missed.  Until you hit 50, you were used to getting a good damage upgrade/spell every 4 or 5 levels.  So really, at 54 or 55 is when I feel we should have gotten the boost in damage to the next set of draughts, not 57.  <br>
<br>
Focus items ARE available now, be happy for that.  AA abilities are available, be happy for that.  Flowing thoughts items, while not TOO common, at least are available.  <br>
<br>
I agree, the class could use some work pre-60, and I agree that with Elnerick's and Garrisons available at 60, I could see that Sunstrike could have been made a level 55 or 57 spell.  But the class is NOT broken just because you don't have/use the available equipment in the game.  I feel there should be more damage focus 3 and 4 items in the game, and that's a better complaint.<br>
<br>
Another thing to look at, as you went from 39 to 44 to 49, not only did the new spell do a lot more damage, but the casting times went up.  Lower cast time spells like draughts will allow you to channel through being hit at a reasonable rate, so you can nuke a mob down while going toe to toe(assuming the mob doesn't have too many HP).  So that 3 second cast on draughts is VERY welcome rather than being stuck with 6+ second nukes.  6 second nukes are nice when you can root/snare/nuke and have no problem getting the spell off, but try that when you are in an XP group and need to cast.<br>
<br>
