<br>
Wizards as a whole should be able to do a percentage of a mob and the big hits were nice to have and see.  But don't discount Ice Comet.  We still have level 56 wizards using IC on Ahkeva hits.<br>
<br>
I personally have Sunstrike, Ice spear of solist.  I don't have GSS or EER.  I mainly use Draught of fire, Draught of thunder (level 61), ice spear, and sword pet.  I have FT1 and 10 AA at level 61.  <br>
<br>
I dont count myself as broken but I do think we are underpowered compared to Mages and sometimes even druids.  Mages in groups can outdamage me with just their pets.  In raids I can usually outdamage the mages because of resists on spells - but if they have their pets out we have had raids saved just because of mage pets.  Druids can outdamage me in certain conditions and seeing consistant 2300+ crits is disappointing.  But that druid has 30+ AA points.<br>
<br>
I have played cleric to 57 (still working on her) and monk (48 now but he is my green farming/explorer).  Every character class can do things differently but I get more requests for my cleric for groups.  Rarely do I get a request for exp group with wizard.  Normally I am asked to help on a raid.  But I do have the capabilities of soloing with the wizard.  The biggest pain is that to do solo in the PoP zones is that I have to have KEI.  I don't NEED bracelets or anything else.  <br>
<br>
I don't care about dieing it is the getting KEI again that I hate.  But I do have the option of soloing where alot of the other classes can't solo at these levels.  (Social skills are there and do work - heck, I deal with Milaru and I am still sane so that should count toward something).  My drawback is I get BORED soloing exp.  I know what quading is - that is how I gained the majority of my exp from 51-61.  My other exp was actually in raids or KS raid groups before they had the raid tool.<br>
<br>
If they really wanted to balance out Wizards more I would think better mana regen or innate standing mana regen - NOT an AA ability.<br>
<br>
If they gave us bigger nukes they definitely would have to adjust agro because you can not stand up to getting agro on these upper end mobs.<br>
<br>
Side Note:  Giants bane is worth the peridot cost if the guild pays for the dots. I don't work to pay someone else.  My normal nuking is around 20k but my best was 32k on Velks before the mod rod nerf.  I don't have Dragon's Bane yet so I still use normal nukes on them.  But I do know that I do excellent damage on the dragons.<br>
<br>
I hope this gives someone enjoyment in reading someone elses opinion.  If you don't agree with anything I said then put your 2 cents in - because that is all any messages on bulletin boards are really worth (if that much).<br>
